## Coding Standards

### Language and Naming Conventions

All code, comments, error messages, log messages, and documentation must be in English.

- **Component Naming**: PascalCase for React components (e.g., `CandidateCard`, `PositionDetails`)
- **Variable Naming**: camelCase for variables and functions (e.g., `candidateId`, `handleSubmit`)
- **Constants Naming**: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE for constants (e.g., `MAX_CANDIDATES_PER_PAGE`, `API_BASE_URL`)
- **Type/Interface Naming**: PascalCase for types and interfaces (e.g., `CandidateData`, `PositionProps`)
- **File Naming**: PascalCase for component files (e.g., `CandidateCard.tsx`), camelCase for utility and slice files (e.g., `candidatesSlice.ts`, `apiUtils.ts`)
- **CSS Class Naming**: kebab-case for CSS classes (e.g., `candidate-card`, `position-details`)
- **Hook Naming**: camelCase starting with "use" prefix (e.g., `useCandidate`, `useAppDispatch`)
- **Slice Naming**: camelCase with "Slice" suffix (e.g., `candidatesSlice`, `positionsSlice`)

```typescript
// Good: All in English with proper conventions
import React, { useState } from 'react';
import { useAppSelector, useAppDispatch } from '../../app/hooks';

type CandidateCardProps = {
    candidate: Candidate;
    index: number;
    onClick: (candidate: Candidate) => void;
};

const CandidateCard: React.FC<CandidateCardProps> = ({ candidate, index, onClick }) => {
    const [isLoading, setIsLoading] = useState(false);

    const handleCardClick = () => {
        onClick(candidate);
    };

    return (
        <div className="candidate-card" onClick={handleCardClick}>
            {/* Component JSX */}
        </div>
    );
};
```

**Error Messages and Console Logs:**

```typescript
// Good: English error messages
catch (error) {
    console.error('Failed to fetch candidates:', error);
    setError('Unable to load candidates. Please try again later.');
}
```

### Component Conventions

#### Functional Components
- **Always use functional components** with hooks
- **All components must be TypeScript** (.tsx files)
- Use **explicit return types** for components

```typescript
import React, { useState, useEffect } from 'react';

type Position = {
    id: number;
    title: string;
    status: 'Open' | 'Closed' | 'Draft';
};

const Positions: React.FC = () => {
    const [positions, setPositions] = useState<Position[]>([]);
    // Component logic
};
```

#### Component Props
- **Define TypeScript types** for all component props
- Use **destructuring** for props
- Include **default values** where appropriate

```typescript
type CandidateCardProps = {
    candidate: Candidate;
    index: number;
    onClick: (candidate: Candidate) => void;
};

const CandidateCard: React.FC<CandidateCardProps> = ({ candidate, index, onClick }) => {
    // Component implementation
};
```

### State Management

#### Redux Toolkit Store Setup

Configure the store with typed hooks for consistent usage across the application.

```typescript
// app/store.ts
import { configureStore } from '@reduxjs/toolkit';
import candidatesReducer from '../features/candidates/candidatesSlice';
import positionsReducer from '../features/positions/positionsSlice';

export const store = configureStore({
    reducer: {
        candidates: candidatesReducer,
        positions: positionsReducer,
    },
});

export type RootState = ReturnType<typeof store.getState>;
export type AppDispatch = typeof store.dispatch;
```

```typescript
// app/hooks.ts
import { useDispatch, useSelector } from 'react-redux';
import type { RootState, AppDispatch } from './store';

export const useAppDispatch = useDispatch.withTypes<AppDispatch>();
export const useAppSelector = useSelector.withTypes<RootState>();
```

#### Redux Slices

Use `createSlice` for all Redux state. Use `createAsyncThunk` for async operations.

```typescript
import { createSlice, createAsyncThunk, PayloadAction } from '@reduxjs/toolkit';

type CandidatesState = {
    items: Candidate[];
    status: 'idle' | 'loading' | 'succeeded' | 'failed';
    error: string | null;
};

const initialState: CandidatesState = {
    items: [],
    status: 'idle',
    error: null,
};

export const fetchCandidates = createAsyncThunk(
    'candidates/fetchCandidates',
    async () => {
        const response = await fetch(`${API_BASE_URL}/candidates`);
        if (!response.ok) {
            throw new Error('Failed to fetch candidates');
        }
        return response.json() as Promise<Candidate[]>;
    }
);

const candidatesSlice = createSlice({
    name: 'candidates',
    initialState,
    reducers: {
        candidateAdded(state, action: PayloadAction<Candidate>) {
            state.items.push(action.payload);
        },
    },
    extraReducers: (builder) => {
        builder
            .addCase(fetchCandidates.pending, (state) => {
                state.status = 'loading';
            })
            .addCase(fetchCandidates.fulfilled, (state, action) => {
                state.status = 'succeeded';
                state.items = action.payload;
            })
            .addCase(fetchCandidates.rejected, (state, action) => {
                state.status = 'failed';
                state.error = action.error.message ?? 'Unknown error';
            });
    },
});

export const { candidateAdded } = candidatesSlice.actions;
export default candidatesSlice.reducer;
```

#### Local State vs Redux State

- **Redux**: Shared/global state, server-fetched data, state needed across routes
- **Local (useState)**: Form inputs, UI toggles, component-specific transient state

#### Loading and Error States
- **Always handle loading states** for async operations
- **Use Redux slice status** fields (`'idle' | 'loading' | 'succeeded' | 'failed'`)
- **Use React Bootstrap Alert** components for user feedback

```typescript
const CandidateList: React.FC = () => {
    const dispatch = useAppDispatch();
    const { items, status, error } = useAppSelector((state) => state.candidates);

    useEffect(() => {
        if (status === 'idle') {
            dispatch(fetchCandidates());
        }
    }, [status, dispatch]);

    if (status === 'loading') return <Spinner animation="border" />;
    if (status === 'failed') return <Alert variant="danger">{error}</Alert>;

    return (
        <ul>
            {items.map((candidate) => (
                <li key={candidate.id}>{candidate.name}</li>
            ))}
        </ul>
    );
};
```

### Service Layer Architecture

#### API Services (when not using RTK Query)
- **Centralize API calls** in service files
- **Export service objects** with grouped methods
- **Handle errors at service level** when appropriate
- **Type all request and response data**

```typescript
const API_BASE_URL = import.meta.env.VITE_API_URL ?? 'http://localhost:8000';

export const positionService = {
    getAllPositions: async (): Promise<Position[]> => {
        const response = await fetch(`${API_BASE_URL}/api/v1/positions`);
        if (!response.ok) {
            throw new Error('Error fetching positions');
        }
        return response.json();
    },

    updatePosition: async (id: number, data: UpdatePositionRequest): Promise<Position> => {
        const response = await fetch(`${API_BASE_URL}/api/v1/positions/${id}`, {
            method: 'PUT',
            headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
            body: JSON.stringify(data),
        });
        if (!response.ok) {
            throw new Error('Error updating position');
        }
        return response.json();
    },
};
```

#### RTK Query (preferred for data fetching)

```typescript
import { createApi, fetchBaseQuery } from '@reduxjs/toolkit/query/react';

export const candidatesApi = createApi({
    reducerPath: 'candidatesApi',
    baseQuery: fetchBaseQuery({ baseUrl: import.meta.env.VITE_API_URL ?? 'http://localhost:8000/api/v1' }),
    tagTypes: ['Candidate'],
    endpoints: (builder) => ({
        getCandidates: builder.query<Candidate[], void>({
            query: () => '/candidates',
            providesTags: ['Candidate'],
        }),
        createCandidate: builder.mutation<Candidate, CreateCandidateRequest>({
            query: (body) => ({ url: '/candidates', method: 'POST', body }),
            invalidatesTags: ['Candidate'],
        }),
    }),
});

export const { useGetCandidatesQuery, useCreateCandidateMutation } = candidatesApi;
```

## UI/UX Standards

### Bootstrap Integration
- Use **React Bootstrap components** instead of plain Bootstrap HTML
- **Import Bootstrap CSS** in the main entry point
- Follow **Bootstrap responsive grid system** (Container, Row, Col)

```typescript
import { Container, Row, Col, Card, Button, Form, Alert, Spinner } from 'react-bootstrap';
```

### Form Handling
- Use **controlled components** for form inputs
- Implement **real-time validation** where appropriate
- **Disable submit buttons** during form submission
- **Clear form state** after successful submission

```tsx
<Form onSubmit={handleSubmit}>
    <Form.Group className="mb-3">
        <Form.Label>Title *</Form.Label>
        <Form.Control
            type="text"
            name="title"
            value={formData.title}
            onChange={handleInputChange}
            required
        />
    </Form.Group>
    <Button type="submit" disabled={saving}>
        {saving ? 'Saving...' : 'Save'}
    </Button>
</Form>
```

### Navigation Patterns
- Use **React Router** for all navigation
- **Implement breadcrumbs** with back navigation
- Use **programmatic navigation** with useNavigate hook
- Define routes centrally in a routes configuration

```typescript
import { useNavigate } from 'react-router-dom';

const navigate = useNavigate();

<Button variant="link" onClick={() => navigate('/')}>
    Back to Dashboard
</Button>
```

### Accessibility
- Include **aria-label** attributes for interactive elements
- Use **semantic HTML** elements
- Ensure **keyboard navigation** support
- Provide **alternative text** for images

```tsx
<Form.Control
    type="text"
    placeholder="Search by title"
    aria-label="Search positions by title"
/>
```

## Testing Standards

### End-to-End Testing with Cypress
- **Test user workflows** rather than implementation details
- Use **data-testid** attributes for reliable element selection
- **Organize tests by feature** (e.g., `candidates.cy.ts`, `positions.cy.ts`)
- **Include API testing** alongside UI testing

```typescript
describe('Positions API - Update', () => {
    beforeEach(() => {
        cy.window().then((win) => {
            win.localStorage.clear();
        });
    });

    it('should update a position successfully', () => {
        const updateData = {
            title: 'Updated Test Position',
            status: 'Open',
        };

        cy.request({
            method: 'PUT',
            url: `${API_URL}/positions/${testPositionId}`,
            body: updateData,
        }).then((response) => {
            expect(response.status).to.eq(200);
            expect(response.body.data.title).to.eq(updateData.title);
        });
    });
});
```

### Test Organization
- **Group related tests** with describe blocks
- **Use descriptive test names** that explain the expected behavior
- **Test both success and error scenarios**
- **Include edge cases** and validation testing
- Use **Vitest** for unit tests of slices, hooks, and utilities

```typescript
// Example Vitest unit test for a Redux slice
import { describe, it, expect } from 'vitest';
import candidatesReducer, { candidateAdded } from './candidatesSlice';

describe('candidatesSlice', () => {
    it('should add a candidate to the list', () => {
        const initialState = { items: [], status: 'idle' as const, error: null };
        const candidate = { id: 1, name: 'John Doe', email: 'john@example.com' };

        const state = candidatesReducer(initialState, candidateAdded(candidate));

        expect(state.items).toHaveLength(1);
        expect(state.items[0]).toEqual(candidate);
    });
});
```

## Configuration Standards

### TypeScript Configuration
- Enable **strict mode** for type checking
- Use **path mapping** with "@/" for cleaner imports
- Configure for **Vite** with appropriate module resolution

```json
{
    "compilerOptions": {
        "target": "ES2020",
        "module": "ESNext",
        "moduleResolution": "bundler",
        "strict": true,
        "jsx": "react-jsx",
        "baseUrl": ".",
        "paths": {
            "@/*": ["src/*"]
        },
        "types": ["vite/client"]
    },
    "include": ["src"]
}
```

### ESLint Configuration
- Extend **eslint:recommended** and **typescript-eslint** rules
- Include **React hooks** rules
- Enforce **consistent code style** across the project

```javascript
module.exports = {
    root: true,
    env: { browser: true, es2020: true },
    extends: [
        'eslint:recommended',
        'plugin:@typescript-eslint/recommended',
        'plugin:react-hooks/recommended',
    ],
    parser: '@typescript-eslint/parser',
    plugins: ['react-refresh'],
    rules: {
        'react-refresh/only-export-components': ['warn', { allowConstantExport: true }],
    },
};
```

### Environment Configuration
- Use **Vite environment variables** prefixed with `VITE_`
- **Separate configurations** for development and production
- **Configure Cypress** with environment-specific settings
- Access env vars via `import.meta.env.VITE_*`

```typescript
// vite.config.ts
import { defineConfig } from 'vite';
import react from '@vitejs/plugin-react';
import path from 'path';

export default defineConfig({
    plugins: [react()],
    resolve: {
        alias: {
            '@': path.resolve(__dirname, './src'),
        },
    },
    server: {
        port: 3000,
    },
});
```

```typescript
// cypress.config.ts
import { defineConfig } from 'cypress';

export default defineConfig({
    e2e: {
        baseUrl: 'http://localhost:3000',
        env: {
            API_URL: 'http://localhost:8000',
        },
    },
});
```

## Performance Best Practices

### Component Optimization
- **Lazy load** route-level components with `React.lazy` and `Suspense`
- **Memoize expensive calculations** with `useMemo`
- **Stabilize callback references** with `useCallback`
- **Extract reusable logic** into custom hooks
- **Use Redux selectors** to minimize unnecessary re-renders

```typescript
import React, { lazy, Suspense } from 'react';
import { Spinner } from 'react-bootstrap';

const CandidateDetails = lazy(() => import('./pages/CandidateDetails'));

<Suspense fallback={<Spinner animation="border" />}>
    <CandidateDetails />
</Suspense>
```

### Bundle Optimization
- **Tree shaking** enabled through Vite
- **Code splitting** at route level with dynamic imports
- **Optimize images** and static assets
- **Analyze bundle size** with `vite-plugin-visualizer`

### API Efficiency
- **Use RTK Query** for automatic caching and deduplication
- **Implement loading states** to improve perceived performance
- **Use optimistic updates** for mutations where appropriate
- **Invalidate cache tags** to keep data fresh after mutations

## Development Workflow

### Git Workflow
- **Feature Branches**: Develop features in separate branches with `-frontend` suffix to avoid conflicts
- **Descriptive Commits**: Write descriptive commit messages in English
- **Code Review**: Code review before merging
- **Small Branches**: Keep branches small and focused

### Development Scripts

```bash
npm run dev            # Vite development server with HMR
npm run build          # Production build
npm run preview        # Preview production build locally
npm run test           # Run Vitest unit tests
npm run lint           # Run ESLint
npm run cypress:open   # Open Cypress test runner
npm run cypress:run    # Run Cypress tests headlessly
```

### Code Quality
- **ESLint validation** before commits
- **TypeScript compilation** without errors (`tsc --noEmit`)
- **All tests passing** before deployment
- **No `any` types** unless explicitly justified

## Migration Strategy

### TypeScript Migration
- **All new code must be TypeScript** — no new `.js` or `.jsx` files
- **Migrate existing JavaScript** files incrementally during refactors
- **Enable strict mode** from the start for new files

### Component Modernization
- **Functional components** over class components
- **Hooks** instead of lifecycle methods
- **Redux Toolkit slices** instead of manual action creators and reducers
- **React Bootstrap** components for UI consistency
- **Responsive design** principles throughout

## Definition of Done (Frontend)

A frontend change is complete when:
- [ ] All new code is TypeScript with proper type annotations
- [ ] Redux state changes use Redux Toolkit slices
- [ ] Components use React Bootstrap for UI consistency
- [ ] Cypress E2E tests cover critical user workflows
- [ ] Unit tests cover slice reducers and utility functions
- [ ] ESLint passes with no errors
- [ ] TypeScript compiles with no errors (`tsc --noEmit`)
- [ ] Loading and error states are handled for all async operations
- [ ] Accessibility attributes are present on interactive elements
- [ ] No Clean Architecture boundary violations in feature modules
